{{Infobox gem | name = Alexander Pushkin | image = | caption = | carats = 320.65 | grams = {{convert|320.65|carat|g|abbr=on}} | color = Colorless | cut = | mine = [[Udachnaya pipe]] | country = {{USSR}}. | found = 1989 | cutter = Raw | original_owner = [[USSR|Soviet]] state. | owner = [[Diamond Fund|Russian Diamond Fund]], [[Moscow Kremlin]]. | value = Never put on sale. }} The '''Alexander Pushkin''' ({{lang-rus|Алекса́ндр Пу́шкин}}) is a 320.65 [[carat (mass)|carat]]<ref name = "FORBESRU">{{cite web|url=http://www.forbes.ru/news/246003-alrosa-dobyla-v-yakutii-almaz-v-235-karat|title=АЛРОСА добыла в Якутии алмаз в 235 карат|publisher=www.forbes.ru|date=9 October 2013|accessdate=30 June 2016}}</ref> [[Diamond color|colorless]]<ref name = "KMRU">{{cite web|url=http://www.km.ru/economics/2012/10/24/ekonomika-i-finansy/695697-v-rossii-dobyli-unikalnyi-almaz-gigant-massoi-bolee-|title=В России добыли уникальный алмаз-гигант массой более 800 карат|publisher=www.km.ru|date=24 October 2012|accessdate=30 June 2016}}</ref> raw [[diamond]], the second largest [[gemstone|gem diamond]] ever found in [[Russia]] or the territory of the former [[USSR]] (after the [[26th Congress of the Communist Party of the Soviet Union (diamond)|26th Congress of the CPSU]]), and one of the [[List of largest rough diamonds|largest in the world]] as of 2016. It was mined at the [[Udachnaya pipe|Udachnaya kimberlitic pipe]] ([[Sakha Republic|Yakutia]], [[Far Eastern Federal District]]) in December 1989<ref name = "PRAVDA">{{cite web|url=http://www.pravdareport.com/news/science/07-08-2003/51710-0/|title=Unique diamond found in Siberia.|publisher=www.pravdareport.com|date=7 August 2003|accessdate=2 July 2016}}</ref> and named after the world-famous Russian writer [[Alexander Pushkin]]. It is kept in the [[Diamond Fund|Russian Diamond Fund]] ([[Moscow Kremlin]].)<ref name = "AWROSRU">{{cite web|url=http://www.awros.ru/kamni/342.html|title=Крупнейшие алмазы, найденные на территории России.|publisher=www.awros.ru|accessdate=30 June 2016}}</ref>
