{{Infobox organization |name = International Science Council |logo = International science council logo.png |logo_size = 250px |headquarters = [[Paris]], [[France]] |type = [[International non-governmental organization|INGO]] |leader_title = President |leader_name = [[Daya Reddy]] |formation = {{Start date and age|2018}} |website = [https://council.science/ council.science] }}
The '''International Science Council''' (ISC) is a non-governmental organization that unites scientific bodies at various levels across the social and natural sciences. The ISC was formed in July 2018 by the merger of the [[International Council for Science]] and the [[International Social Science Council|International Social Science Council (ISSC)]], making it one of the largest organisations of this type.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.unesco.org/news/two-main-science-councils-merge-address-complex-global-challenges|title=Two main Science Councils merge to address complex global challenges|website=UNESCO|language=en|access-date=2018-10-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://council.science/about-us/|title=About us|publisher=International Science Council|language=en|accessdate=20 Oct 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=McBean|first=Gordon|last2=Martinelli|first2=Alberto|date=2017-11-24|title=Blurring disciplinary boundaries|url=http://science.sciencemag.org/content/358/6366/975|journal=Science|language=en|volume=358|issue=6366|pages=975–975|doi=10.1126/science.aar4320|issn=0036-8075|pmid=29170207}}</ref>
Daya Reddy from the [[University of Cape Town]] was elected inaugural president of the board.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://theecologist.org/2018/jul/19/paris-launches-international-science-council-aims-rebuild-trust-science|title=Paris launches the International Science Council with aims to rebuild trust in science|work=The Ecologist|access-date=2018-10-21|language=en}}</ref> Heide Hackmann serves as CEO.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://council.science/about-us/main-secretariat|title=About Us|work=International Science Council|access-date=2018-10-21}}</ref>
